details.product_descriptions: AEROSPACE 60 AMT | Gladen Clear Dynamic Energetic Sound Image Tweeters FEATURES:  The AEROSPACE 60 AMT tweeter has a clear, dynamic - energetic sound image, a very good impulse response and a high low distortion. The Air Motion Transformer (AMT) represents a loudspeaker concept that does not require a classic voice coil.On a thin Kapton foil (12 - 25 µm thick), a specially designed conductor track made of thin aluminum (also only 12 - 25 µm thick) is worked out via complex etching processes, which has a meandering course.To achieve high manufacturing precision, the foil is folded by hand using special tools. Unlike conventional tweeter domes, the folded AMT diaphragm in the loudspeaker does not make any movement from the front and to the rear to produce the tones. The movement takes place in the folds, that is, laterally, similar to a bellows. This causes the air in the convolutions to accelerate and exit the front.One advantage of this technology is that the diaphragm area is larger than the visible area and thus takes up less space.Coupled with the light weight of the diaphragm, this results in a detailed and dynamic reproduction.All housing parts are elaborately CNC machined, nickel plated, powder coated and then laser engraved. The aluminum frame can be dismantled to allow an even more compact installation. The special copper cable with silicone sheathing and braid protection is directly connected to the membrane to avoid unnecessary transitions or materials in the signal path. details.product_descriptions: Big-time sound for the great outdoors Can-Am's Maverick X3 is a high-performance side-by-side with plenty of power, and MB Quart's Stage 3 kit will make your Maverick sound as good as it performs. With a marine digital media receiver, 6-1/2' marine speakers, a 2-channel amp, a mono sub amp, and a 10' subwoofer, this system will add even more fun to your off-road adventures. MB Quart designed this package to fit right into your Maverick, with no cutting and minimal hassle. It also comes with all the parts and pieces needed for a smooth, hassle-free installation. Each component is tough enough for trail duty, so you won't have to worry about your system getting swamped. A rugged receiver that fits right in The MB Quart GMR-LED digital media receiver packs a lot of cool stuff into a compact, outdoor-ready package that's made for your Maverick. This AM/FM/WB receiver features built-in Bluetooth, so you can pair up quickly and stream music stored on your phone. If you have an Apple device, you'll appreciate the convenience of Apple Control. If you prefer to plug in, you'll find an AUX input and a charging USB input. If you want to expand your system later, the GMR-LED features a full set of preamp outputs, along with a handy camera input. This kit includes a custom-designed dash panel that holds the receiver and blends into your Maverick's dash. Dash speakers made for your Maverick The package includes a pair of NP1-116 Nautic marine speakers that are built for off-road and marine use. The durable poly cones withstand moisture and sunlight, as do the 1' titanium dome tweeters. They're really easy to install, too, thanks to the made-for-the-Maverick X3 speaker enclosures included in this kit. They're easy to install and the left speaker panel works with your Maverick's Smart-Lok(tm). Get your power from a 2-channel amp MB Quart's NA2-400.2 amplifier packs a lot of power into a small package that's perfect for powersports applications.
